\
 ~ luk-3 derived from the Tarski-Bernays-Wajsberg axioms. This theorem, along with ~ re1luk1 and ~ re1luk2 proves that ~ tbw-ax1 , ~ tbw-ax2 , ~ tbw-ax3 , and ~ tbw-ax4 , with ~ ax-mp can be used as a complete axiom system for all of propositional calculus.
